args: Okay, I think we're good. Security seems\npretty lax—I don't even see any guards.
You're being unusually cautious, Luca.\nThis town dangerous or something?
No idea. That's WHY I'm being cautious.

This place is the perfect distance from
both the Halidom and the capital, not
too far, not too close...but it's inside
Empire territory.
I was worried we might see some folks\nfrom Emile's corner sniffin' around, but it\nlooks like we're in the clear on that, too.
And I don't see any sign of Shadows,\neither. This should work nicely as a\nstaging ground for our Jail heist!
Now we just need to scope out the town\nuntil we carry out the mission.
Then let's start by checking restaurants!\nThere's gotta be something around here\nwhere I can grab some mad eats.
Not so fast. We usually start our heists\nby scouting potential escape routes and\nmapping the layout of back alleys.
And we can totally look into that stuff!\nBut food comes first.
Sheesh, nothing ever phases this guy.\nReminds me of someone else I know...
C'mon, Mona! Shake a tail already!
Bwa ha ha! Oy, that's a good'un!\nAin't nobody 'ere what can catch ME!
Slow down there, hero! We're supposed\nto be keeping a low profile.
Aaaand...he's gone. Welp, guess I just\ngotta roll with the punches.
Har har! Ain't nobody can keep up with\nol' Lightnin' Legs Hollywood!

You've got a lot of nerve to be stealing
from people when there's a real thief like
me standing right there. Now be a good
little crook and let me drag you back.
Wait, yer a fellow five-finger discounter?\nWhatcha nickin' me for, then? Ain't ya got\nno honor? What about the thief's code?!

That's not a real thing—plus, me and my
fellow phantom thieves would never do
anything as uncool as stealing from
innocent people like you did!
That still don't tell me why yer 'ere\ngettin' up in my business!
Because the Phantom Thieves of Hearts \nhelp people in trouble! And in this case,\nyou're the trouble.
All right, that's enough! Ya may be a fellow\nfilcher, but I bet chips to chunder yer arse\nkicks as well as any other! Haaaaah!
Heh. You might want to actually look at\nyour foe when you take a swing like that.
Hey, Mona! Where'd you... Oh, whoa.\nYou already caught the thief? Nice!
Mewheheh! That's what happens when\nyou try to dance with a REAL thief.
Can't believe I got pummeled by\nsome stupid cat... Uuurgh...
Are you two thinking what I'm thinking?
